:{"defaultMessage":"(optional)"},"(previous session)":{"defaultMessage":"(previous session)"},"(required)":{"defaultMessage":"(required)"},"+ Range constraint":{"defaultMessage":"+ Range constraint"},"+ Search Service":{"defaultMessage":"+ Search Service"},"+ Value":{"defaultMessage":"+ Value"},"+{remainingCount} more":{"defaultMessage":"+{remainingCount} more"},"0 minutes":{"defaultMessage":"0 minutes"},"1 File":{"defaultMessage":"1 File"},"1 file {isCut, select, true {cut} other {copied}}. You can now paste into another folder or workspace.":{"defaultMessage":"1 file {isCut, select, true {cut} other {copied}}. You can now paste into another folder or workspace."},"1 of 2: Setting up service ({percent}% Complete)":{"defaultMessage":"1 of 2: Setting up service ({percent}% Complete)"},"2 of 2: Connecting kernel ({percent}% Complete)":{"defaultMessage":"2 of 2: Connecting kernel ({percent}% Complete)"},"A dimension is a column used to group or filter results. Example: region in Orders lets you ask Cortex Analyst, \\"Show me revenue by region.\\"":{"defaultMessage":"A dimension is a column used to group or filter results. Example: region in Orders lets you ask Cortex Analyst, \\"Show me revenue by region.\\""},"A fact is a raw numeric field that can be aggregated. Example: order_amount in Orders lets Cortex Analyst calculate related things such as total revenue.":{"defaultMessage":"A fact is a raw numeric field that can be aggregated. Example: order_amount in Orders lets Cortex Analyst calculate related things such as total revenue."},"A filter is a saved condition to reuse in queries. Example: Defining active_customers as status = \'active\' and user_type = \'Customer\' lets you ask things like, \\"Average spend for active customers?\\" and Cortex Analyst will use this filter more deterministically.":{"defaultMessage":"A filter is a saved condition to reuse in queries. Example: Defining active_customers as status = \'active\' and user_type = \'Customer\' lets you ask things like, \\"Average spend for active customers?\\" and Cortex Analyst will use this filter more deterministically."},"A list with numbering.":{"defaultMessage":"A list with numbering."},"A logical table is a simplified, business-friendly version of a Snowflake table. Cortex Analyst only sees the key columns you expose. Example: the Customers logical table may include customer_id, region, and signup_date.":{"defaultMessage":"A logical table is a simplified, business-friendly version of a Snowflake table. Cortex Analyst only sees the key columns you expose. Example: the Customers logical table may include customer_id, region, and signup_date."},"A metric is an aggregate defined on a single table - used for consistent calculations across your organization. Example: SUM(order_amount) / COUNT(order_id). Cortex Analyst automatically reuses this definition when you ask related questions.":{"defaultMessage":"A metric is an aggregate defined on a single table - used for consistent calculations across your organization. Example: SUM(order_amount) / COUNT(order_id). Cortex Analyst automatically reuses this definition when you ask related questions."},"A project named \'\'{projectName}\'\' already exists in this location.":{"defaultMessage":"A project named \'\'{projectName}\'\' already exists in this location."},"A relationship defines how two logical tables join. Example: Orders.customer_id → Customers.customer_id lets Cortex Analyst answer \\"spend per customer by region.\\" Relationships require the right column to be a primary or unique key because Cortex Analyst only generates many-to-one or one-to-one relationships. For many-to-many, consider creating a shared dimension in a view and then defining two many-to-one relationships.":{"defaultMessage":"A relationship defines how two logical tables join. Example: Orders.customer_id → Customers.customer_id lets Cortex Analyst answer \\"spend per customer by region.\\" Relationships require the right column to be a primary or unique key because Cortex Analyst only generates many-to-one or one-to-one relationships. For many-to-many, consider creating a shared dimension in a view and then defining two many-to-one relationships."},"A service with this name already exists, please choose another.":{"defaultMessage":"A service with this name already exists, please choose another."},"A simple bulleted list.":{"defaultMessage":"A simple bulleted list."},"A time dimension is a date or timestamp column so Cortex Analyst can handle time-based questions. Example: order_date lets you ask, \\"How many orders in July 2025?\\"":{"defaultMessage":"A time dimension is a date or timestamp column so Cortex Analyst can handle time-based questions. Example: order_date lets you ask, \\"How many orders in July 2025?\\""},"A valid project is required in order to plan. {projectName} doesn\'t exist. Would you like to create it?":{"defaultMessage":"A valid project is required in order to plan. {projectName} doesn\'t exist. Would you like to create it?"},"A workspace with this name already exists":{"defaultMessage":"A workspace with this name already exists"},"ACTION":{"defaultMessage":"ACTION"},"AI":{"defaultMessage":"AI"},"AI & ML":{"defaultMessage":"AI & ML"},"AI Code Suggestions enabled":{"defaultMessage":"AI Code Suggestions enabled"},"AI Studio":{"defaultMessage":"AI Studio"},"AI code suggestions":{"defaultMessage":"AI code suggestions"},"AI code suggestions disabled":{"defaultMessage":"AI code suggestions disabled"},"ALTER DBT PROJECT finished without error":{"defaultMessage":"ALTER DBT PROJECT finished without error"},"API Integration":{"defaultMessage":"API Integration"},"API Integration {name} created":{"defaultMessage":"API Integration {name} created"},"API integration":{"defaultMessage":"API integration"},"API integration is required to create a workspace from Git repository. Please create one or request access to existing ones.":{"defaultMessage":"API integration is required to create a workspace from